From 5083eef0089dd51981bd34453897dd91078e7f8e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Darrick J. Wong" <djwong@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 22 Dec 2021 14:19:18 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] xfs: map unwritten blocks in XFS_IOC_{ALLOC,FREE}SP just like
 fallocate

commit 102af6edfd3a372db6e229177762a91f552e5f5e from linux-stable
commit 983d8e60f50806f90534cc5373d0ce867e5aaf79 upstream.

The old ALLOCSP/FREESP ioctls in XFS can be used to preallocate space at
the end of files, just like fallocate and RESVSP.  Make the behavior
consistent with the other ioctls.

Reported-by: Kirill Tkhai <ktkhai@virtuozzo.com>
Signed-off-by: Darrick J. Wong <djwong@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Darrick J. Wong <darrick.wong@oracle.com>
Reviewed-by: Dave Chinner <dchinner@redhat.com>
Reviewed-by: Eric Sandeen <sandeen@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
[SG: backport of 102af6e from linux-5.4.y branch of linux-stable]
Signed-off-by: Stefan Ghinea <stefan.ghinea@windriver.com>
---
 fs/xfs/xfs_ioctl.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/fs/xfs/xfs_ioctl.c b/fs/xfs/xfs_ioctl.c
index 8a9719104a8f..86fd0d3373c0 100644
--- a/fs/xfs/xfs_ioctl.c
+++ b/fs/xfs/xfs_ioctl.c
@@ -695,7 +695,8 @@ xfs_ioc_space(
 		flags |= XFS_PREALLOC_CLEAR;
 		if (bf->l_start > XFS_ISIZE(ip)) {
 			error = xfs_alloc_file_space(ip, XFS_ISIZE(ip),
-					bf->l_start - XFS_ISIZE(ip), 0);
+					bf->l_start - XFS_ISIZE(ip),
+					XFS_BMAPI_PREALLOC);
 			if (error)
 				goto out_unlock;
 		}
